dict.string:
On the Fifteenth of December, 1992, I was born in the university hospital of Düsseldorf. The regional Capital of North Rhine-Westphalia has a variety points of interest. From big shopping boulevards like the KÖ (Königsallee) to the Kunstpalast (Artpalace) there are enough spare time possibilities without getting bored quickly.
I have lived in Düsseldorf for a couple of years before my parents and I moved to Kaarst. It is a rather small city with around 40.000 citizens. I have spent most of my life here. Although it might be not as big as Düsseldorf it is at least as beautiful.
I was born in Düsseldorf, Germany, where I lived a couple of years.
